                            <comment id="13203505" author="rhusar" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 19:24:02 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=matthew.casperson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;matthew.casperson&quot;&gt;Matthew Casperson&lt;/a&gt; For the sake of completeness, please fill in the affected version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13203515" author="mcasperson" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 20:29:37 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rhusar&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rhusar&quot;&gt;Radoslav Husar&lt;/a&gt; - Unfortunately it seems that I can&apos;t edit the ticket any more. It is for WildFly 10.0.0.Final.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13204512" author="rhusar" created="Thu, 12 May 2016 14:34:30 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem here is the missing dependency establishement (i.e. JNDI lookup doesn&apos;t guarantee any lifecycle coupling). This needs to ideally make use of capabilities API, expose datasource reference in the model (rather than a property) and also require a change in JGroups to be able to supply datasource directly (rather than JNDI lookup).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13237694" author="rhusar" created="Fri, 13 May 2016 17:38:03 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/JGRP-2063&quot; title=&quot;JDBC_PING: allow supplying dataSource object directly (e.g. via after_creation_hook)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JGRP-2063&quot;&gt;JGRP-2063&lt;/a&gt; for changes that need to be done in JGroups directly.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

